column11: The data you carry is vital to the remaining Federation fleet. You'll need supplies for the journey, so make sure to explore each sector before moving on to the next. But get to the exit before the pursuing Rebel fleet can catch up!  TIP: Oxygen -  If the ship's room color changes from tan to red, it means you're losing oxygen. Crew will be damaged and fires will burn out in rooms with red hazard stripes.
You scan the battlefield, and are able to salvage some useful material from the wreckage.
With most of the fire under control, the scientists are able to help secure the station. They offer you their sincere gratitude and a generous reward.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

It's unlikely the Rock's impressive immune system is susceptible to a human virus so you send it in. It is able to intimidate the workers long enough for the colony forces to set up a quarantine. Their leaders offer a reward and assure you they will try to find a cure as soon as possible.
You happen upon an abandoned mining site. A few mining drones were left behind and could be repurposed.
The station is a storage site for various resources. You salvage everything possible.
You find yourself surrounded by a group of mysterious alien vessels. They hail you and apparently have some valuable technology for sale.

column11: You jump into an unremarkable system. No life signs detected within scanning range.
They transmit the space dock's coordinates. Added a quest marker to the next sector!
Nebulas were always dangerous places. Many electronics fail in these clouds. You will have to tread lightly.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You find yourself surrounded by a group of mysterious alien vessels. They hail you and apparently have some valuable technology for sale.
column12: System: teleporter, battery, mind, Weapon: MISSILES BURST, MISSILES HULL, BEAM HULL, Augment: EXPLOSIVE REPLICATOR, ADV SCANNERS, TELEPORT HEAL,

column11: You nervously glance out the windows but the only thing to greet you is more clouds and silence.
Without active sensors you have no other option but to look out of the view-ports in apprehension. It's eerily quiet.
There's nothing here, save for vast swirls of gas reflecting rays from a distant sun.
The station is a storage site for various resources. You salvage everything possible.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.
You see a small station nearby and feel the shudder of shots ringing through the ship. You can't be sure without sensors, but it seems there may be intruders on the ship!
The Rock grudgingly transfer control of their helm to you and you steer them to a thinner part of the nebula. They're not sure what to think, but transfer over some supplies all the same.
This Long-Range Beacon is almost hidden within a nebula. When the FTL Drive is charged you can jump to the next Sector.
You have arrived in Engi space. The fall of the Federation has brought tough times for these robotic lifeforms, but they're usually willing to help.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
A message arrives: Your scrap, ours. Our weapons for you. You're about to raise the shields when you realize it's just an Engi trader looking for a trade.
column12: System: drones, battery, hacking, Augment: ADV SCANNERS, HACKING STUN, ZOLTAN BYPASS, Drone: REPAIR, DRONE SHIELD, DEFENSE 1, Crew: Engi, Human, Human,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The Engi seem to have avoided this particular node, along with every other life-form. You keep your eyes peeled for reasons why, but spin up the FTL without event.
Federation sympathizers contact you as you arrive. We know your mission should be secret, so don't ask how we know about it. Take this schematic, it's all we can do to help.

None of your attempts to communicate seem to work: they just stare at you silently. As you prepare to leave, one of the creatures canters forward and forcefully nudges you away from the ship. He seems to want you to follow him. Eventually, they guide you to an old Engi ship's crash site. Inside you are able to find and reactivate an Engi!
The gases that make up the nebulas in this sector threaten to impair your systems; but you have to press on.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You feel naked without functioning sensors. You half expect a Rebel ship to appear from behind a cloud at any moment, but none come.
Your crew are constantly looking out of the windows, checking for hostiles. They jump at every creak and moan of the ship. The tension is almost palpable...
Seeing a trade depot set up near the beacon implies there is an alien settlement on some nearby rock. You decide to check out their wares.
column12: System: drones, teleporter, mind, Augment: FTL BOOSTER, ZOLTAN BYPASS, FLEET DISTRACTION,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Searching the remains, you find that the cargo was military-grade Drone Schematics! You bring them aboard to install in your ship.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
You see a small station nearby and feel the shudder of shots ringing through the ship. You can't be sure without sensors, but it seems there may be intruders on the ship!
The station was apparently designed to outfit Rebel ships with Drone Systems. You find a functioning Schematic.
You follow the faint signatures and find them floating not too far away into the nebula. Thrilled to be found by friendlies, they come on board and abandon their wrecked ship.
You can't see anything through the thick gases surrounding your ship. Without knowing what is out there, all you can do is wait for your FTL to charge.
The debris implies that the ship was carrying Drone Schematics, but unfortunately nothing remains. You do find functioning Drone Parts, however.
The Rock people have a particularly aggressive stance toward alien races trespassing in their space. You should tread carefully here.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
With the local Rock settlements so unwilling to trade with other life forms, an opportunistic Mantis crew has postponed its piracy activities and set up shop to catch any passing trade.
column12: System: medbay, battery, mind, Weapon: LASER BURST 3, SHOTGUN, BOMB STUN,

column11: You begin the salvage operation but before long your crew warns you of an approaching ship. You hasten to leave before they get within firing range.
The Rock tolerate few aliens in their space, but even they seem to respect the wisdom of the Zoltan - a few of them have established a trading post in the husk of an abandoned capital ship.
column12: System: drones, medbay, teleporter, Augment: ADV SCANNERS, ZOLTAN BYPASS, TELEPORT HEAL,

column11: The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
In the time it took you to eliminate the Mantis ship the Rock must have repaired their FTL drive and jumped away. You pick the bones of both Mantis vessels.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
They are thrilled with your success and offer you a reward.
Thank you, this will help greatly.
You have arrived in Engi space. The Mantis have been threatening the Engi core worlds, but you should be able to stock up for your journey.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.
Thank you for the aid! I'm an arms dealer that usually only works with Rebels, but considering the circumstances I'll make an exception.

You find a pirate ship, damaged and abandoned. You salvage what you can and move on.
You take a hopeful trip to the Clone Bay, and to your relief a clone is already prepared for the lost crewmember.
An Engi ship hails: Engine upgrade necessary for travel home. Sale of equipment necessary for engine upgrade.

column11: Thank you for your business.
Thank you, this will help greatly.
A settlement still loyal to the Federation hails your ship. They have prepared a weapon to aid your escape from the Rebels.
At one point this was one of the most commonly traveled sectors. Knowing that, the Rebels have stationed a number of fleets here. Be careful.
The ship explodes, leaving behind a substantial collection of useful scrap material.

As you are leaving you detect an interesting Federation ship signal. Apparently the Rebels were reverse engineering the advanced weaponry on a prototype Federation cruiser. You don't know how they captured the ship intact but you program its FTL drive to return the ship to the nearest Federation base. You just hope it gets there unharmed.
You receive generic advertisements from a nearby public ship-yard. It seems they are willing to work on any ship, not only those of Rebel hue.

column11: You discover a re-supply station used by Rebels and civilians alike. You transmit your fake ship identification and for once, they don't seem to recognize your ship. You try to assume the air of a local as you prepare to dock.

Their ship breaks apart and you are relieved to know that you are still one step ahead of the fleet.
The ship breaks apart and you feel relief in the knowledge that you will hopefully still be one step ahead of the fleet.

You arrive to find yourself extremely close to a star. You receive a message from a pirate ship, I'm glad you arrived; our ship is damaged and we were getting desperate... I hope you don't mind if we take yours. Hostiles detected on board our ship!
You happen upon the remains of a space station. It has been mostly picked clean but there appears to be a few materials that will aid you in your mission.

Tully responds, It's settled. The Rebels will be here in a matter of moments. We will do what we can to hold off their warships but you must succeed in destroying this flagship. Your current outpost can provide some repairs and fuel, and the other repair stations can provide aid as well. Good luck.
There's no time to salvage all of the wreck, the fleet is still nearby. Get ready to jump!

You arrive near the Federation Base to find the bulk of their fleet skirmishing with Rebel forces. You hang back near the far side of the moon to avoid the conflict. There's not much you can do to help in that battle, and your mission holds the key to turn the tide of the war. You prepare to face the Flagship.
A forward construction station is in the process of repairing damaged warships. Your command codes convince them to do a quick patch job on your ship.
